# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# FICSIT Foreman environment configuration
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values appropriate to your machine.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Game data location (Phase 1 — MCP server) ──────────────────────────────
# FICSIT Foreman reads Satisfactory's machine-readable game data from `en-US.json`
# (found under `<game install>/CommunityResources/Docs/`). There are two ways to
# point FICSIT Foreman at it; SATISFACTORY_DOCS_PATH takes priority if both are set.

# Option A (highest priority): full path directly to the docs file.
# Use this when the game files are not mounted at their usual location — for
# example on a headless VM where the file was copied across manually.
# SATISFACTORY_DOCS_PATH=/home/you/foreman/game-data/en-US.json

# Option B: the Satisfactory install root. FICSIT Foreman appends
# `CommunityResources/Docs/en-US.json` (falling back to the pre-1.0 `Docs.json`).
# Example paths:
#   Steam  (Windows): C:/Program Files (x86)/Steam/steamapps/common/Satisfactory
#   Epic   (Windows): C:/Program Files/Epic Games/SatisfactoryExperimental
#   Steam  (Linux):   /home/you/.steam/steam/steamapps/common/Satisfactory
# SATISFACTORY_GAME_DIR=/path/to/Satisfactory

# If neither variable is set, the MCP server starts with an empty dataset and
# logs a warning — it will not crash.

# ── Save-game data (optional — mcp-save-game) ───────────────────────────────
# The optional save-game MCP server reads a Satisfactory save file (.sav) to
# expose live pioneer progress (inventory, unlocks, collectibles). It is DISABLED
# by default: the compose service only starts under the `save-game` profile, e.g.
#   SAVE_FILE_PATH=/path/to/MySave.sav docker compose --profile save-game up -d
# Set this to the full path of the .sav to read (in-container path under Docker).
# Saves live under `<...>/FactoryGame/Saved/SaveGames/<id>/`. Leave unset to skip.
# SAVE_FILE_PATH=/saves/MySave.sav

# ── MCP transport ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How the server exposes itself. Default is stdio (what Claude Desktop spawns);
# there is no network port in that mode. Set to 'http' to listen on a network
# port instead (Streamable HTTP). HTTP mode has NO authentication — keep it on a
# trusted localhost/LAN only.
# MCP_TRANSPORT=stdio          # 'stdio' (default) or 'http'
# MCP_HTTP_HOST=0.0.0.0        # bind host for http mode (0.0.0.0 = all interfaces)
# MCP_HTTP_PORT=8723           # port for http mode

# ── Foreman backend (Phase 2 — packages/server) ─────────────────────────────
# The backend proxies chat to an LLM provider with the foreman persona, calls
# the MCP game-data tools, and persists work orders.

# LLM provider: 'anthropic' (native Claude, default) or 'openai' (the OpenAI
# Chat Completions API — also covers Azure OpenAI, OpenRouter, and Google's
# OpenAI-compatible endpoint via LLM_BASE_URL).
# LLM_PROVIDER=anthropic

# Hosted-tier API key for the chosen provider. If set, the server uses it for
# clients that don't supply their own. If unset, every client MUST pass its own
# key in the 'x-anthropic-api-key' request header (free tier). Either way works.
# LLM_API_KEY=...
# (Back-compat: when LLM_PROVIDER is anthropic, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is still read;
#  when openai, OPENAI_API_KEY is read.)

# Model + token bounds. Defaults: claude-sonnet-4-6 (anthropic) / gpt-4.1 (openai).
# LLM_MODEL=
# LLM_MAX_TOKENS=4096

# Cheaper model for background session summarisation. Defaults:
# claude-haiku-4-5 (anthropic) / gpt-4.1-mini (openai). Once a conversation rolls
# past HISTORY_WINDOW*2 messages the server condenses older context into a
# running summary carried forward in the system prompt.
# LLM_SUMMARY_MODEL=
# LLM_SUMMARY_MAX_TOKENS=512

# Base URL for the OpenAI-compatible provider (ignored for anthropic). Examples:
#   OpenAI:      https://api.openai.com/v1   (the default — leave unset)
#   OpenRouter:  https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
#   Gemini:      https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai
# LLM_BASE_URL=

# Legacy env (still honoured when LLM_PROVIDER is anthropic):
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# ANTHROPIC_MAX_TOKENS=4096
# ANTHROPIC_SUMMARY_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5
# ANTHROPIC_SUMMARY_MAX_TOKENS=512

# Per-request override: a client that sends its own key (header below) may also
# choose provider/model/baseUrl per message via the chat POST body fields
# { provider, model, baseUrl }. Without a client key the server defaults are used.

# Where the backend reaches the game-data MCP server. In Docker Compose this is
# the mcp-game-data service name; for bare-metal dev it defaults to 127.0.0.1.
# MCP_URL=http://mcp-game-data:8723/mcp    # default (bare metal): http://127.0.0.1:8723/mcp

# Optional save-game MCP server. When set, its tools (player location, remaining
# collectibles, unlocks, inventory) are merged into the foreman's tool surface so
# it can populate location-aware work-order opportunities. Leave unset to run on
# game-data tools alone. The save-game MCP listens on 8726 in http mode.
# SAVE_MCP_URL=http://mcp-save-game:8726/mcp   # bare metal: http://127.0.0.1:8726/mcp

# Backend HTTP bind + port.
# HOST=0.0.0.0                   # default 0.0.0.0
# PORT=8724                      # default 8724

# Database. SQLite for local dev; swap for a Postgres URL in production.
# DATABASE_URL=file:./dev.db     # Docker default: file:/data/foreman.db
# For Postgres, set a postgres:// URL AND change the datasource provider in
# packages/server/prisma/schema.prisma to "postgresql" (the schema is portable —
# complex fields are stored as JSON-encoded TEXT), then run `prisma migrate deploy`.
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://foreman:password@postgres:5432/foreman

# ── Accounts & authentication (packages/server) ─────────────────────────────
# Auth is required to use the app. Email + password is the first factor; sessions
# are HttpOnly cookies (no token is stored in the browser). BYO LLM keys stay
# client-side as before.
#
# BETTER_AUTH_SECRET signs session cookies. If unset, the server generates a
# strong secret on first start and persists it next to the database (in the data
# volume), so single-node deployments work out of the box and sessions survive
# restarts. SET IT EXPLICITLY (e.g. `openssl rand -base64 32`) for multi-instance
# deployments or Postgres, where a shared, stable secret is required.
# BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=a-long-random-string
#
# The public origin the app is served from. Needed for correct cookies/redirects
# behind a reverse proxy; if unset the origin is derived from the request.
# BETTER_AUTH_URL=https://foreman.example.com
#
# Optional comma-separated allow list of origins permitted to make credentialed
# requests (only needed for cross-origin setups; same-origin needs nothing).
# AUTH_TRUSTED_ORIGINS=https://foreman.example.com

# How many of the most recent messages to send with each chat request.
# HISTORY_WINDOW=20              # default 20

# Header a free-tier client uses to pass its own Anthropic key.
# CLIENT_KEY_HEADER=x-anthropic-api-key   # default

# Override the foreman system prompt location (defaults to the bundled file).
# SYSTEM_PROMPT_PATH=/app/SYSTEM_PROMPT.md
